{code}
I created a file called "as.zip" located in directory "a" which is located in directory "test".
I used "test/a" as Location, and I used "*.zip" as Copy Pattern - the same way as it is described in [this document|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO40/Configuring+a+job%27s+build+artifacts].
{code}

However, the artifact didn't get published.

When configuring the JUnit parser, the field "Specify custom results directories" has as an example an ant glob "**/test-reports/*.xml" - which is a glob of files, not directories, and the task does not find test results unless the files end with the "xml" extension.

This works:
{code}
**/Test/*.xml
{code}

This doesn't:
{code}
**/Test/*.testlog
{code}

Even though the files are identical except for the filename extension.

Bamboo logs:
{code}
...
28-Apr-2012 17:04:16	Starting task 'JUnit Parser' of type 'com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.testresultparser:task.testresultparser.junit'
28-Apr-2012 17:04:16	Parsing test results...
28-Apr-2012 17:04:16	Failing task since test cases were expected but none were found.
28-Apr-2012 17:04:16	Finished task 'JUnit Parser'
...
{code}

If I click the nav-bar to change between build runs, the URL is something like this:
{noformat}
https://confluence-bamboo.atlassian.com/build/result/gotoBuildResult.action?returnUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fconfluence-bamboo.atlassian.com%2Fbrowse%2FCONFSTAB-T5PG-260%2Flog&buildKey=CONFSTAB-T5PG&buildNumber=261
{noformat}
Which, btw, is really annoying if you want to just copy the link and paste it elsewhere. But much worse it very often results in a redirect loop error in chrome like this:

{quote}

This webpage has a redirect loop
The webpage at https://confluence-bamboo.atlassian.com/build/result/gotoBuildResult.action?returnUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fconfluence-bamboo.atlassian.com%2Fbrowse%2FCONFSTAB-T5PG-260%2Flog&buildKey=CONFSTAB-T5PG&buildNumber=261 has resulted in too many redirects. Clearing your cookies for this site or allowing third-party cookies may fix the problem. If not, it is possibly a server configuration issue and not a problem with your computer.
Here are some suggestions:
Reload this webpage later.
Learn more about this problem.
{quote}

I thought this issue was already reported but I can't find it.

